The National Working Committee (NWC) of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has appointed former Senate President, Adolphus Wabara, as Chairman Lagos State Congresses Appeal Committee. PDP in a statement by its National Publicity Secretary, Kola Ologunagba, Wednesday, explained that the committee is to consider appeals arising from the conduct of the State Congress in Lagos State. The opposition party also appointed Sen. Jarigbe Agom Jarigbe as Secretary of the committee. Other members of the Committee are Dr Akilu Indabawa, Hajiya Inna Maryam Ciroma, Chief Emmanuel Ogidi, Hon. Aro Bamidele and Barr Oji Zawo. According to the statement, the exercise is scheduled to hold from Thursday, March 3 to Friday, March 4, 2022, at the PDP National Secretariat, Wadata Plaza, Wuse Zone 5, Abuja.